            <title>[SPARK-44185] Inconsistent path qualifying between catalog and data operations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-44185</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For example&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CREATE TABLE statement with relative LOCATION will infer schema from files from the directory relative to the current working directory and store the directory relative to the warehouse path.&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CTAS statement with relative LOCATION cannot assert empty root path as it checks the wrong path it will finally use.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;DataframeWriter does not qualify the path before checking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
